§ Results ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The ❬moment generating function❭ ⦉

  ‖ of a real-valued random variable is ⦉

  ‖ the function mapping real numbers to ⦉

  ‖ the expectation of the exponential ⦉

  ‖ of the product of that real number ⦉

  ‖ with the random variable. ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $(X, 𝒜, μ)$ be a probability space. ⦉

  ‖ Let $f$ be a real-valued random variable on $X$. ⦉

  ‖ Let $R$ denote the real numbers. ⦉

  ‖ For each $t ∈ R$, denote by $tf$ the function $x ↦ tf(x)$. ⦉

  ‖ Similarly, denote by $e^{tf}$ the funciton $x ↦ e^{tf(x)}$. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ Denote the moment generating function of $f$ by $m_f: R →
    R$. ⦉

  ‖ We defined it by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ m_f(t) = 𝗘(e^{tf}). ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉
